{"type":"message","id":"92e11f73","parentId":"a42a55ec","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:17:49.376Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**It's back!** 🎉\n\nMission Control is now running and responding with HTTP 200 on port 3000. Here's what happened:\n\n- The old Vite process (PID 29957) had been running since **Thursday** but lost its port binding — it was a zombie process consuming CPU but not serving anything.\n- I killed the stale processes and used `launchctl kickstart -k` to restart the LaunchAgent.\n- After the 30-second throttle interval, it came back up cleanly.\n\nYou should be able to access it at **http://localhost:3000** now. Give it a try! 🐒"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":190,"output":144,"cacheRead":21888,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":22222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780057059231,"responseId":"gen-1780057059-hMfZDQet8Skx46vWImGj"}}
