{"type":"message","id":"f75d0779","parentId":"1b1c0a51","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:56:12.970Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both paths return 200. The images DO load. So the sprite issue is NOT a path problem — it's a rendering issue. The user sees empty boxes. Let me look at the Spacestation component more carefully — the Dashboard uses `Spacestation.tsx` which has its own `AgentSprite` component, while the AgentOffice uses `StationRoom.tsx`.\n\nWait — looking at the Dashboard code, it renders `<AgentOffice>` which renders `<StationRoom>` with `agentSprite={sprite}`. The StationRoom renders `<img src={agentSprite} ...>` with `className=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\"`. The SSR'd HTML shows `<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>` — **no `src` attribute!**\n\nLet me verify:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"5eaa5601-77bb-4677-99e8-ad29861a1f67","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<img[^>]*>' | head -20","timeout":15},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<img[^>]*>' | head -20\", \"timeout\": 15}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":366,"output":239,"cacheRead":79488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80093,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059334526,"responseId":"gen-1780059337-VW2f7IitP0Eujll4fW73"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d0225d8","parentId":"f75d0779","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:56:14.371Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5eaa5601-77bb-4677-99e8-ad29861a1f67","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<img src=\"/src/assets/sprite-monkey-idle-4x-v2.png\" alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"h-7 w-7 rounded-full border border-violet/50 object-cover\"/>\n<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Life Support Officer\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Systems Engineer\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Station Archivist\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1366,"aggregated":"<img src=\"/src/assets/sprite-monkey-idle-4x-v2.png\" alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"h-7 w-7 rounded-full border border-violet/50 object-cover\"/>\n<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Life Support Officer\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Systems Engineer\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Station Archivist\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059374371}}
{"type":"message","id":"aef4732d","parentId":"2d0225d8","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:56:39.589Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Found the sprite bug!** The sidebar `<img>` has `src=\"/src/assets/sprite-monkey-idle-4x-v2.png\"` but the StationRoom agent sprites have **no `src` attribute at all** — they render as `<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>`.\n\nThis means `agentSprite` (the `sprite` prop) is **empty string** on the server side. The issue is in how `SPRITES` is populated in `AgentOffice.tsx` — it's done in a `useEffect` which only runs on the client, so the SSR render gets empty strings.\n\nLet me verify this theory:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2e789956-5284-4b2d-b83f-3bf80819b407","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && sed -n '95,115p' src/components/AgentOffice.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && sed -n '95,115p' src/components/AgentOffice.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":527,"output":211,"cacheRead":79744,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80482,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059374373,"responseId":"gen-1780059374-pMruvHh7iuzme0o0YdDq"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd92aee2","parentId":"aef4732d","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:56:39.636Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"2e789956-5284-4b2d-b83f-3bf80819b407","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"}, []);\n  // Always live — no toggle\n  const [nowRunning, setNowRunning] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [upNext, setUpNext] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [chatter, setChatter] = useState(\"\");\n  // Always live mode — no ambient timer needed\n\n  // Load sprites from crew\n  useEffect(() => {\n    CREW.forEach(c => {\n      SPRITES[c.id] = { idle: c.sprites.idle, working: c.sprites.working, walking: c.sprites.walking, away: c.sprites.idle };\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  // Live data is always used directly\n\n  // Dispatch live data updates (but don't override seeded initial data on first render)\n  const initialDataSeeded = useRef(false);\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!initialDataSeeded.current) {\n      initialDataSeeded.current = true;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"}, []);\n  // Always live — no toggle\n  const [nowRunning, setNowRunning] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [upNext, setUpNext] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [chatter, setChatter] = useState(\"\");\n  // Always live mode — no ambient timer needed\n\n  // Load sprites from crew\n  useEffect(() => {\n    CREW.forEach(c => {\n      SPRITES[c.id] = { idle: c.sprites.idle, working: c.sprites.working, walking: c.sprites.walking, away: c.sprites.idle };\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  // Live data is always used directly\n\n  // Dispatch live data updates (but don't override seeded initial data on first render)\n  const initialDataSeeded = useRef(false);\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!initialDataSeeded.current) {\n      initialDataSeeded.current = true;","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059399636}}
{"type":"message","id":"3d2b3354","parentId":"bd92aee2","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:57:13.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Confirmed!** The `SPRITES` object is populated inside `useEffect(() => {...}, [])` which doesn't run during SSR. The SSR render sees `SPRITES` as an empty object, so `SPRITES[room.occupantId]?.idle` returns `undefined`, and the `<img src={undefined}>` renders without a `src` attribute.\n\nThe fix: populate `SPRITES` outside of `useEffect`, at module level or during render.\n\nNow let me also understand issue #2 — the Scheduler page. The SSR returns the route fine (match ID `schedulerscheduler`), the HTML shows only a spinner, and the `scheduler.tsx` has a `loading` state defaulting to true via `useCronData()`. Let me check what `useCronData` returns:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"240ae7a8-72cf-4ad3-8411-573e5cbfa347","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"bd48f61c-2632-4ad8-b855-05ebf426b93e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":435,"output":255,"cacheRead":80256,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80946,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059399639,"responseId":"gen-1780059399-16vQYSMte149FuQ0QgIw"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2eb82b1a","parentId":"3d2b3354","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:57:13.267Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"240ae7a8-72cf-4ad3-8411-573e5cbfa347","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useState, useCallback, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport type { OpenClawCronJob } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport interface CronError {\n  id: string;\n  jobName: string;\n  jobId: string;\n  jobEnabled: boolean;\n  consecutiveErrors: number;\n  lastError: string;\n  lastErrorReason: string;\n  lastRunAt: string;\n  status: \"new\" | \"in_progress\" | \"completed\" | \"skipped\";\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CronData {\n  jobs: OpenClawCronJob[];\n  errors: CronError[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  toggling: string | null;\n  result: { id: string; message: string } | null;\n  fetchCrons: () => void;\n  handleToggle: (job: OpenClawCronJob) => Promise<void>;\n  updateErrorStatus: (errorId: string, newStatus: CronError[\"status\"]) => void;\n}\n\n// ── Hook ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function useCronData(): CronData {\n  const [jobs, setJobs] = useState<OpenClawCronJob[]>([]);\n  const [errors, setErrors] = useState<CronError[]>([]);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [toggling, setToggling] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [result, setResult] = useState<{ id: string; message: string } | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchCrons = useCallback(() => {\n    // Fetch both cron jobs and saved error statuses in parallel\n    Promise.all([\n      fetch(\"/api/crons\").then((res) => res.json()),\n      fetch(\"/api/cron-errors\").then((res) => res.json()).catch(() => []),\n    ])\n      .then(([cronJobsData, savedErrors]) => {\n        const cronJobs = cronJobsData as OpenClawCronJob[];\n        setJobs(cronJobs);\n\n        const savedMap = new Map(\n          (savedErrors as Record<string, unknown>[]).map((e) => [e.id, e.status as CronError[\"status\"]])\n        );\n\n        // Extract errors from jobs, merge with saved statuses\n        const errorItems: CronError[] = cronJobs\n          .filter((j) => (j.consecutiveErrors ?? 0) > 0 || j.status === \"error\")\n          .map((j) => {\n            const id = `err-${j.id}`;\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id);\n            // Determine the effective status:\n            // - If job is still failing AND was previously investigated → keep in_progress\n            // - If job is still failing AND was resolved/skipped → the fix didn't work,\n            //   show as \"new\" again (re-escalate)\n            // - If job is still failing with no saved status → show as \"new\"\n            let status: CronError[\"status\"] = \"new\";\n            if (savedStatus === \"in_progress\") {\n              status = \"in_progress\"; // preserve investigation state\n            }\n            // Note: completed/skipped are intentionally NOT preserved here.\n            // If the job fails again after being resolved, it shows as a new error.\n            // This is the correct behavior — the previous resolution didn't fix it.\n            return {\n              id,\n              jobName: j.name,\n              jobId: j.id,\n              jobEnabled: j.enabled,\n              consecutiveErrors: j.consecutiveErrors ?? 0,\n              lastError: j.lastError ?? \"\",\n              lastErrorReason: j.lastErrorReason ?? \"\",\n              lastRunAt: j.lastRun,\n              status,\n              createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n            };\n          })\n          // Only show errors that are new or in_progress (not completed/skipped)\n          .filter((e) => e.status === \"new\" || e.status === \"in_progress\");\n\n        // Auto-clear + merge: remove errors whose jobs have recovered\n        // (consecutiveErrors === 0 and status !== \"error\"), merge existing\n        // in-memory statuses with fresh data, and add any new errors.\n        const activeErrorJobIds = new Set(errorItems.map((e) => e.jobId));\n        setErrors((prev) => {\n          const freshIds = new Set(errorItems.map((e) => e.id));\n          const prevIds = new Set(prev.map((e) => e.id));\n\n          // Start with existing errors: keep only those still active,\n          // merging fresh data while preserving in-memory status\n          const merged = prev\n            .filter((e) => {\n              if (freshIds.has(e.id)) return true; // still failing, in fresh list\n              if (!activeErrorJobIds.has(e.jobId)) return false; // job recovered → auto-clear\n              return true;\n            })\n            .map((e) => {\n              const fresh = errorItems.find((f) => f.id === e.id);\n              return fresh ? { ...fresh, status: e.status } : e;\n            });\n\n          // Add any brand-new errors not in previous state\n          const mergedIds = new Set(merged.map((e) => e.id));\n          const newItems = errorItems.filter((e) => !mergedIds.has(e.id) && !prevIds.has(e.id));\n\n          return [...merged, ...newItems];\n        });\n\n        setLoading(false);\n      })\n      .catch((err) => {\n        console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to fetch crons:\", err);\n        setLoading(false);\n      });\n  }, []);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetchCrons();\n    const interval = setInterval(fetchCrons, 5000);\n    return () => clearInterval(interval);\n  }, [fetchCrons]);\n\n  const handleToggle = useCallback(async (job: OpenClawCronJob) => {\n    setToggling(job.id);\n    setResult(null);\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch(\"/api/cron-toggle\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify({ id: job.id, action: job.enabled ? \"disable\" : \"enable\" }),\n      });\n      const data = await res.json();\n      if (data.ok) {\n        setJobs((prev) =>\n          prev.map((j) =>\n            j.id === job.id ? { ...j, enabled: !job.enabled } : j\n          )\n        );\n        setResult({ id: job.id, message: data.message || (job.enabled ? \"Disabled\" : \"Enabled\") });\n      } else {\n        setResult({ id: job.id, message: `Failed: ${data.error || \"Unknown error\"}` });\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      setResult({ id: job.id, message: `Failed: ${err}` });\n    }\n    setToggling(null);\n    setTimeout(() => setResult(null), 3000);\n  }, []);\n\n  const updateErrorStatus = useCallback((errorId: string, newStatus: CronError[\"status\"]) => {\n    const error = errors.find((e) => e.id === errorId);\n    // If completing or skipping, remove from feed immediately (don't wait for next poll)\n    if (newStatus === \"completed\" || newStatus === \"skipped\") {\n      setErrors((prev) => prev.filter((e) => e.id !== errorId));\n    } else {\n      setErrors((prev) =>\n        prev.map((e) =>\n          e.id === errorId ? { ...e, status: newStatus } : e\n        )\n      );\n    }\n    // Persist to server\n    fetch(\"/api/cron-errors\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ errorId, status: newStatus }),\n    }).catch((err) => console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to save error status:\", err));\n\n    // When investigating, auto-create a task on the Tasks page\n    if (newStatus === \"in_progress\" && error) {\n      const taskTitle = `[Investigate] ${error.jobName}: ${error.lastErrorReason || error.lastError}`;\n      const task = {\n        id: `err-${errorId}`,\n        title: taskTitle,\n        assignee: \"monkey\",\n        status: \"in_progress\",\n        priority: \"P2\",\n        ts: \"just now\",\n        note: `Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: ${error.jobName} (${error.jobId})\\nError: ${error.lastError}\\nConsecutive errors: ${error.consecutiveErrors}`,\n        history: [{\n          ts: new Date().toISOString(),\n          action: \"created\",\n          actor: \"system\",\n          details: `Auto-created from error feed for ${error.jobName}`,\n        }],\n        errorId: errorId,\n        jobId: error.jobId,\n      };\n      fetch(\"/api/tasks/add\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify(task),\n      }).then((res) => res.json()).then((data) => {\n        if (data.ok) {\n          console.log(\"[SchedulerPage] Created investigation task:\", taskTitle);\n        } else {\n          console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to create task:\", data.message);\n        }\n      }).catch((err) => console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to create task:\", err));\n    }\n\n    // When marking resolved, update the error status to completed\n    if (newStatus === \"completed\" && error) {\n      console.log(\"[SchedulerPage] Error marked as completed:\", error.jobName);\n    }\n  }, [errors]);\n\n  return {\n    jobs,\n    errors,\n    loading,\n    toggling,\n    result,\n    fetchCrons,\n    handleToggle,\n    updateErrorStatus,\n  };\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059433266}}
{"type":"message","id":"42617ef2","parentId":"2eb82b1a","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:57:13.267Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"bd48f61c-2632-4ad8-b855-05ebf426b93e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type { OpenClawCronJob } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { CronError } from \"./useCronData\";\nimport { Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport { Power, Clock, AlertTriangle, CheckCircle, Loader2 } from \"lucide-react\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface CronJobCardProps {\n  job: OpenClawCronJob;\n  isToggling: boolean;\n  hasResult: boolean;\n  resultMessage: string | null;\n  hasActiveError: boolean;\n  onToggle: (job: OpenClawCronJob) => void;\n}\n\n// ── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function CronJobCard({\n  job,\n  isToggling,\n  hasResult,\n  resultMessage,\n  hasActiveError,\n  onToggle,\n}: CronJobCardProps) {\n  return (\n    <div\n      className={`rounded-xl border bg-card/60 px-5 py-4 transition-all ${\n        job.enabled\n          ? \"border-border border-l-4 border-l-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n          : \"border-border/40 border-l-4 border-l-border/30 opacity-70\"\n      }`}\n    >\n      <div className=\"flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap\">\n          <h3 className=\"font-semibold\">{job.name}</h3>\n          <Pill variant={job.enabled ? \"online\" : \"default\"}>\n            {job.enabled ? \"ACTIVE\" : \"DISABLED\"}\n          </Pill>\n          {hasActiveError && (\n            <Pill variant=\"warning\">⚠ {job.consecutiveErrors ?? 0} error{job.consecutiveErrors ?? 0 > 1 ? \"s\" : \"\"}</Pill>\n          )}\n        </div>\n\n        <button\n          onClick={() => onToggle(job)}\n          disabled={isToggling}\n          className={`relative inline-flex h-6 w-11 items-center rounded-full transition-colors shrink-0 ${\n            job.enabled\n              ? \"bg-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n              : \"bg-muted-foreground/30\"\n          } ${isToggling ? \"opacity-50 cursor-wait\" : \"cursor-pointer\"}`}\n        >\n          {isToggling ? (\n            <Loader2 className=\"h-3 w-3 text-white absolute left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 animate-spin\" />\n          ) : (\n            <span\n              className={`inline-block h-4 w-4 transform rounded-full bg-white transition-transform ${\n                job.enabled ? \"translate-x-6\" : \"translate-x-1\"\n              }`}\n            />\n          )}\n        </button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div className=\"mt-2 flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground\">\n        <Clock className=\"h-3 w-3\" />\n        <span>{job.schedule}</span>\n      </div>\n\n      {job.message && (\n        <div className=\"mt-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 line-clamp-2\">\n          {job.message}\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      <div className=\"mt-3 flex items-center gap-4 font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground/50\">\n        {job.lastRun !== \"—\" && (\n          <span>Last: {new Date(job.lastRun).toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"2-digit\", month: \"short\", hour: \"2-digit\", minute: \"2-digit\" })}</span>\n        )}\n        {job.nextRun !== \"—\" && job.enabled && (\n          <span>Next: {new Date(job.nextRun).toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"2-digit\", month: \"short\", hour: \"2-digit\", minute: \"2-digit\" })}</span>\n        )}\n      </div>\n\n      {hasResult && resultMessage && (\n        <div className={`mt-2 text-xs ${resultMessage.startsWith(\"Failed\") ? \"text-destructive\" : \"text-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"}`}>\n          {resultMessage}\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"import type { OpenClawCronJob } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { CronError } from \"./useCronData\";\nimport { Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport { Power, Clock, AlertTriangle, CheckCircle, Loader2 } from \"lucide-react\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface CronJobCardProps {\n  job: OpenClawCronJob;\n  isToggling: boolean;\n  hasResult: boolean;\n  resultMessage: string | null;\n  hasActiveError: boolean;\n  onToggle: (job: OpenClawCronJob) => void;\n}\n\n// ── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function CronJobCard({\n  job,\n  isToggling,\n  hasResult,\n  resultMessage,\n  hasActiveError,\n  onToggle,\n}: CronJobCardProps) {\n  return (\n    <div\n      className={`rounded-xl border bg-card/60 px-5 py-4 transition-all ${\n        job.enabled\n          ? \"border-border border-l-4 border-l-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n          : \"border-border/40 border-l-4 border-l-border/30 opacity-70\"\n      }`}\n    >\n      <div className=\"flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap\">\n          <h3 className=\"font-semibold\">{job.name}</h3>\n          <Pill variant={job.enabled ? \"online\" : \"default\"}>\n            {job.enabled ? \"ACTIVE\" : \"DISABLED\"}\n          </Pill>\n          {hasActiveError && (\n            <Pill variant=\"warning\">⚠ {job.consecutiveErrors ?? 0} error{job.consecutiveErrors ?? 0 > 1 ? \"s\" : \"\"}</Pill>\n          )}\n        </div>\n\n        <button\n          onClick={() => onToggle(job)}\n          disabled={isToggling}\n          className={`relative inline-flex h-6 w-11 items-center rounded-full transition-colors shrink-0 ${\n            job.enabled\n              ? \"bg-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n              : \"bg-muted-foreground/30\"\n          } ${isToggling ? \"opacity-50 cursor-wait\" : \"cursor-pointer\"}`}\n        >\n          {isToggling ? (\n            <Loader2 className=\"h-3 w-3 text-white absolute left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 animate-spin\" />\n          ) : (\n            <span\n              className={`inline-block h-4 w-4 transform rounded-full bg-white transition-transform ${\n                job.enabled ? \"translate-x-6\" : \"translate-x-1\"\n              }`}\n            />\n          )}\n        </button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div className=\"mt-2 flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground\">\n        <Clock className=\"h-3 w-3\" />\n        <span>{job.schedule}</span>\n      </div>\n\n      {job.message && (\n        <div className=\"mt-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 line-clamp-2\">\n          {job.message}\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      <div className=\"mt-3 flex items-center gap-4 font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground/50\">\n        {job.lastRun !== \"—\" && (\n          <span>Last: {new Date(job.lastRun).toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"2-digit\", month: \"short\", hour: \"2-digit\", minute: \"2-digit\" })}</span>\n        )}\n        {job.nextRun !== \"—\" && job.enabled && (\n          <span>Next: {new Date(job.nextRun).toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"2-digit\", month: \"short\", hour: \"2-digit\", minute: \"2-digit\" })}</span>\n        )}\n      </div>\n\n      {hasResult && resultMessage && (\n        <div className={`mt-2 text-xs ${resultMessage.startsWith(\"Failed\") ? \"text-destructive\" : \"text-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"}`}>\n          {resultMessage}\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059433267}}
{"type":"message","id":"65e2acb3","parentId":"42617ef2","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:57:37.047Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK so the Scheduler page loads data client-side via `useCronData` which fetches `/api/crons` and `/api/cron-errors`. The page renders fine on the server (shows a spinner), but the client-side fetch might be failing. Let me check the API endpoint:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"938f4684-d5a3-41c6-b788-1d1e18a6d0d9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/crons | head -5","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/crons | head -5\", \"timeout\": 10}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3d0ffd64-76f1-43a7-be63-3eb03452f39c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/api/crons && echo \"\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/api/cron-errors && echo \"\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://localhost:3000/api/crons && echo \\\"\\\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://localhost:3000/api/cron-errors && echo \\\"\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":3359,"output":203,"cacheRead":80640,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":84202,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059433270,"responseId":"gen-1780059433-CokNOLIGBX99RgiCU5RE"}}
