{"type":"message","id":"faa9ba35","parentId":"3662bca4","timestamp":"2026-05-29T13:00:18.684Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK the route tree looks fine — `SchedulerRoute` has `id: '/scheduler'` and imports from `./routes/scheduler`. The `schedulerscheduler` in the HTML route match is because TanStack Router's route ID format for the match includes the full path. Let me look at this differently.\n\nActually, re-reading the HTML more carefully: `i: \"schedulerscheduler\"` — this is unusual. Normal route IDs from the generated tree would be `/scheduler`. The double `scheduler` suggests the route got registered twice or the ID got concatenated.\n\nWait — the SSR HTML for `/scheduler` shows `matches: [{i: \"__root__\", ...}, {i: \"schedulerscheduler\", ...}]`. The route ID should be `/scheduler` based on `routeTree.gen.ts`. But it shows `schedulerscheduler`. This is very wrong.\n\nLet me check if there might be another scheduler-related route file:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"df713060-6ed3-4619-b80f-864762d99193","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && find src -name \"*scheduler*\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\"","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && find src -name \\\"*scheduler*\\\" -not -path \\\"*/node_modules/*\\\"\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6332769d-8084-49c0-b60f-961f1116a703","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && grep -rn \"createFileRoute.*scheduler\" src/ --include=\"*.tsx\" --include=\"*.ts\" | grep -v node_modules","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && grep -rn \\\"createFileRoute.*scheduler\\\" src/ --include=\\\"*.tsx\\\" --include=\\\"*.ts\\\" | grep -v node_modules\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"i