{"type":"message","id":"f2bdb39a","parentId":"e38fcaf7","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:11:19.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, I see the issue now. The `RoomCanvas` component draws rooms on a `<canvas>` element using JavaScript drawing functions. This is NOT an image — it's a canvas that gets drawn via `useEffect`. The canvas renders client-side only (drawing happens in `useEffect`). This is by design — the rooms are pixel art drawn on canvas.\n\nThe user says room backgrounds are \"not showing\" and \"were previously rendering but now gone.\" Let me check if the canvas is actually rendering by looking at the HTML output:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2b1591a1-ba44-4d53-aa8d-3a74325f137b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<canvas[^>]*>' | head -10","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<canvas[^>]*>' | head -10\", \"timeout\": 10}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0e67abfe-f98f-40dc-b75b-f342782ff3d6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -c 'canvas'","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -c 'canvas'\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":17546,"output":200,"cacheRead":115328,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":133074,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780063837481,"responseId":"gen-1780063837-01CxBQl7MqWLLzUAOrWI"}}
