{"type":"message","id":"945910b3","parentId":"3cc876be","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:12:03.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The canvas elements exist in the HTML. There are 4 main room canvases (768×512) — one per room. The canvas drawing happens client-side via `useEffect`. The canvas should work... unless there's a hydration error causing React to not mount the client-side component.\n\nWait — the user said \"room backgrounds... are not showing. The room images that were previously rendering are now gone.\" Let me think about this differently. Maybe the rooms were previously using `<img>` tags with room PNG files, and at some point switched to canvas? Let me check git history:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"72e14a40-0cac-4bcb-9227-2f0eace317f6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline -20","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline -20\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":567,"output":165,"cacheRead":132864,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":133596,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780063881083,"responseId":"gen-1780063881-hbeqegYWS6AN8V5FEkf5"}}
