{"type":"message","id":"7a7977f5","parentId":"268ae0d7","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:13:37.257Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No backlog tasks. Let me continue the fixes. I need to investigate the room backgrounds and sprite grey boxes.\n\nLet me first check what the current AgentOffice code looks like after my last edit:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"aad47639-b835-46a2-8bd7-7602967bc0ee","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":10,"offset":90,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AgentOffice.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 10, \"offset\": 90, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AgentOffice.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":313,"output":92,"cacheRead":134016,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":134421,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780063979629,"responseId":"gen-1780063979-PgFIM5nfb8YdODRD6K66"}}
{"type":"message","id":"96b4fe7d","parentId":"7a7977f5","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:13:37.297Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"aad47639-b835-46a2-8bd7-7602967bc0ee","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"      initialAgents.forEach(agent => {\n        const activity: AgentActivity = agent.status === \"active\" && agent.tasksActive > 0 ? \"working\" : \"idle\";\n        dispatch({ type: \"SET_AGENT_ACTIVITY\", agentId: agent.id, activity });\n      });\n    }\n  }, []);\n  // Always live — no toggle\n  const [nowRunning, setNowRunning] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [upNext, setUpNext] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [chatter, setChatter] = useState(\"\");\n\n[244 more lines in file. Use offset=100 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780064017297}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ec6fe80","parentId":"96b4fe7d","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:13:58.690Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"5b04f28f-df98-4eb2-b759-162f934dde2b","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":60,"offset":100,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AgentOffice.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 60, \"offset\": 100, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AgentOffice.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":295,"output":54,"cacheRead":134272,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":134621,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780064017301,"responseId":"gen-1780064017-aecjMaEdKqhUW7nDC23Q"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc71b473","parentId":"5ec6fe80","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:13:58.726Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5b04f28f-df98-4eb2-b759-162f934dde2b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  // Always live mode — no ambient timer needed\n\n  // Load sprites from crew (outside useEffect so SSR gets the values)\n  CREW.forEach(c => {\n    SPRITES[c.id] = { idle: c.sprites.idle, working: c.sprites.working, walking: c.sprites.walking, away: c.sprites.idle };\n  });\n\n  // Live data is always used directly\n\n  // Dispatch live data updates (but don't override seeded initial data on first render)\n  const initialDataSeeded = useRef(false);\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!initialDataSeeded.current) {\n      initialDataSeeded.current = true;\n      return; // Skip first render — initial data already seeded\n    }\n    liveData.agents.forEach(agent => {\n      const activity: AgentActivity = agent.status === \"working\" ? \"working\" : agent.status === \"collaborating\" ? \"collaborating\" : agent.status === \"idle\" ? \"idle\" : \"idle\";\n      dispatch({ type: \"SET_AGENT_ACTIVITY\", agentId: agent.id, activity });\n    });\n    dispatch({ type: \"SET_MOOD\", mood: liveData.stationMood });\n    dispatch({ type: \"SET_ALERT\", level: liveData.alertLevel });\n  }, [liveData]);\n\n  // No ambient mode — always use live data\n\n  // Update running/up-next\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const running = liveData.agents\n      .filter(a => a.status === \"working\" || a.status === \"collaborating\")\n      .map(a => `${a.name}: ${a.currentAction || \"Active\"}`);\n    setNowRunning(running.length > 0 ? running : [\"All systems nominal — standing by\"]);\n    setUpNext([\"Memory consolidation\", \"Wiki lint check\", \"Git auto-commit\"]);\n  }, [liveData]);\n\n  // Station chatter\n  useEffect(() => {\n    setChatter(getRandomChatter());\n    const interval = setInterval(() => setChatter(getRandomChatter()), 8000);\n    return () => clearInterval(interval);\n  }, []);\n\n  // Collaboration data for AgentTravel\n  const collaborations = liveData.agents\n    .filter(a => a.status === \"collaborating\")\n    .map((a, i) => ({\n      id: `collab-${a.id}-${i}`,\n      agents: [a.id, \"monkey\"] as [string, string],\n      fromRoom: a.id === \"monkey\" ? \"command\" : a.id === \"lifesupport\" ? \"security\" : a.id === \"engineer\" ? \"workshop\" : \"archive\",\n      toRoom: \"command\",\n      sprite: SPRITES[a.id]?.walking || SPRITES[a.id]?.idle || \"\",\n    }));\n\n  const moodColors: Record<string, string> = {\n    calm: \"text-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\",\n    busy: \"text-violet\",\n    alert: \"text-warning\",\n    critical: \"text-destructive\",\n  };\n\n\n[184 more lines in file. Use offset=160 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780064038726}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0652b41","parentId":"cc71b473","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:14:35.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, so the `SPRITES` initialization at line 103 is now at module level (outside `useEffect`) — good, that's the sprite fix. But wait, this is inside the component function, not at module level. It runs on every render and on SSR. That should be fine.\n\nNow let me understand the room background issue. The `RoomCanvas` component draws rooms on `<canvas>` using `useEffect`. It's client-side only. The user says room backgrounds \"were previously rendering but now gone.\" Maybe the issue is that `RoomCanvas` is wrapped in a way that it doesn't render at all during SSR, and then client-side hydration doesn't mount it properly.\n\nLet me look at what StationRoom renders for the background:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"45f49c63-2aad-4e74-bc30-4917f2331eb6","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":148,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 15, \"offset\": 148, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":770,"output":211,"cacheRead":134528,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":135509,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780064038730,"responseId":"gen-1780064038-ZLropEXt1UcJscz34hbB"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e5bea5a","parentId":"f0652b41","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:14:35.379Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"45f49c63-2aad-4e74-bc30-4917f2331eb6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n  // CSS animation class based on agent state\n  const spriteAnimClass = isWorking ? \"agent-working\" : isAsleep ? \"agent-sleeping\" : isWalk ? \"agent-walking\" : agentState === \"thinking\" ? \"agent-thinking\" : \"agent-idle\";\n  const bubbleAnimClass = isWorking ? \"bubble-visible\" : \"bubble-visible\";\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative overflow-hidden bg-card/10\">\n      <div className=\"relative\">\n        {useCanvas ? (\n          <RoomCanvas room={ROOM_TYPE_MAP[roomId] || \"command\"} className=\"w-full h-auto\" />\n        ) : (\n          <img src={bgImage} alt={label} className=\"w-full h-auto\" style={{ imageRendering: \"pixelated\" }} />\n        )}\n\n        <div className=\"absolute top-1 left-1 font-mono text-[7px] tracking-[0.15em] text-muted-foreground/50 bg-background/40 px-1.5 py-0.5\">{label}</div>\n\n[118 more lines in file. Use offset=163 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780064075378}}
{"type":"message","id":"749e7c38","parentId":"9e5bea5a","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:15:09.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So when `useCanvas={true}` (which AgentOffice passes), it renders `<RoomCanvas>` which is a `<canvas>` element drawn via `useEffect`. This should work — the SSR would render an empty canvas, and the client would draw on it.\n\nBut maybe the user is saying the room backgrounds were previously showing as **image files** (PNG background images) and now they're gone. Let me check if there was a recent change that removed room image rendering:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"99e44fbb-9acd-4633-b655-37c7afea89e2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline --all -- src/components/StationRoom.tsx | head -5","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline --all -- src/components/StationRoom.tsx | head -5\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0be00f2b-9cc4-4816-a612-b6efdb167089","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline --all -- src/components/RoomCanvas.tsx | head -5","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline --all -- src/components/RoomCanvas.tsx | head -5\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":606,"output":200,"cacheRead":135168,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":135974,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780064075383,"responseId":"gen-1780064075-07hiuofVSgFxdVGSN8Fm"}}
