{"type":"compaction","id":"f7494bc3","parentId":"6e3c32be","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.522Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Fix agent sprites missing on Dashboard and Agent Office\n- Resolve Scheduler page not loading issue\n- Fix missing room backgrounds\n- Remove grey boxes around sprites\n- Address scheduler spinning wheel issue\n- Commit and push changes\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- (none)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- ✅ **Sprite Fix**: Moved `SPRITES` initialization from `useEffect` to module scope to resolve SSR hydration issue\n- ✅ **Scheduler Page**: Resolved route conflict by moving non-route files from `src/routes/scheduler/` to `src/components/scheduler/`\n- ✅ **Verified Routes**: All routes (`/`, `/visual`, `/scheduler`, `/tasks`, `/team`) return 200\n- ✅ **Sprite Verification**: All 4 agent sprites show valid `src` paths in HTML\n- ✅ **Commit**: Changes committed with message fixing sprites and scheduler issues\n\n### In Progress\n- 🔄 **Room Backgrounds**: Debugging missing Command HQ, Security Bay, Engineering, Archive images\n- 🔄 **Sprite Styling**: Removing unintended grey boxes around sprites\n- 🔄 **Scheduler Hydration**: Investigating lingering loading wheel despite SSR success\n\n### Blocked\n- Room background drawing via `RoomCanvas.tsx` not rendering expected output after changes\n- Loader wheel persists on Scheduler page despite updated build\n\n## Key Decisions\n**[Sprite SSR Fix]**: **Move** `SPRITES` initialization to module scope instead of client-only `useEffect` to ensure server renders valid image URLs  \n**[Scheduler Route Conflicts]**: **Eliminate** directory/file collision by relocating non-route files from `src/routes/scheduler/` to `src/components/scheduler/`\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Investigate canvas rendering logic in `RoomCanvas.tsx` for missing room backgrounds\n2. Audit `AgentOffice.tsx` for unintended border/wrapper components causing grey boxes\n3. Confirm Scheduler page hydration works with font loading/shadow CSS adjustments\n4. Verify latest build deployed to dev server\n5. Push changes to Git remote\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Sprite Code**:  \n  `AgentOffice.tsx` incorrectly populates `SPRITES` client-side only  \n  `Spacestation.tsx` references room images via `assets/room-*.png` imports  \n- **Scheduler Code**:  \n  Conflicting `src/routes/scheduler/` dir + `src/routes/scheduler.tsx` caused route collision  \n- **Canvas Issue**:  \n  `RoomCanvas.tsx` uses JS canvas drawing (no img src) causing hydration mismatch on SSR\n\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user asked the assistant to read the `HEARTBEAT.md` file located at `/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md`, follow its instructions strictly, and respond with `HEARTBEAT_OK` if there is nothing that needs attention.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Executed a command to read `data/tasks.json` and determined there are **0 backlog tasks**.\n- Confirmed no heartbeat tasks to pick up, so proceeded with the ongoing UI fixes the assistant was already working on.\n- Inspected `AgentOffice.tsx` to verify the `SPRITES` initialization was correctly moved outside of `useEffect`.\n- Examined `StationRoom.tsx` to understand how room backgrounds are rendered (via `<RoomCanvas>` with client‑side canvas drawing).\n- Checked recent Git commits to see if any recent refactor might have broken background rendering; found only comment changes.\n- Reviewed `RoomCanvas.tsx` diff – only non‑functional warning comment added.\n- Looked at CSS definitions for sprite animation classes and confirmed no background or border styles that would cause a grey box.\n- Queried the running server (`curl http://localhost:3000/`) to verify the presence of the four room containers and the `<canvas>` elements.\n- Inspected the rendered HTML for the scheduler route, confirming the page loads and contains expected markup.\n- Updated an internal plan with steps: investigating room backgrounds, fixing grey sprite boxes, addressing scheduler spinner, and committing fixes.\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The assistant has identified that **room backgrounds are drawn on a `<canvas>` via client‑side `useEffect`**, so they appear only after hydration.\n- The **grey box around sprites** is likely due to the room container’s `bg-card/10` background showing through transparent sprite PNGs, not from explicit CSS borders.\n- The **scheduler spinner** may be persisting because of a client‑side hydration issue, even though SSR markup looks correct.\n- The assistant’s next actions (in the retained suffix) will focus on confirming these hypotheses, possibly adjusting CSS or hydration logic, and finalizing the UI fixes.\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/styles.css\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AgentOffice.tsx\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/scheduler.tsx\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"376b745b","tokensBefore":184752,"details":{"readFiles":["/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json","/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx","/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/styles.css"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AgentOffice.tsx","/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/scheduler.tsx"]},"fromHook":false}
