{"type":"message","id":"a0090643","parentId":"c0d6218c","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both paths return 200. The images DO load. So the sprite issue is NOT a path problem — it's a rendering issue. The user sees empty boxes. Let me look at the Spacestation component more carefully — the Dashboard uses `Spacestation.tsx` which has its own `AgentSprite` component, while the AgentOffice uses `StationRoom.tsx`.\n\nWait — looking at the Dashboard code, it renders `<AgentOffice>` which renders `<StationRoom>` with `agentSprite={sprite}`. The StationRoom renders `<img src={agentSprite} ...>` with `className=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\"`. The SSR'd HTML shows `<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>` — **no `src` attribute!**\n\nLet me verify:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"5eaa5601-77bb-4677-99e8-ad29861a1f67","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<img[^>]*>' | head -20","timeout":15},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '<img[^>]*>' | head -20\", \"timeout\": 15}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":366,"output":239,"cacheRead":79488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80093,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059334526,"responseId":"gen-1780059337-VW2f7IitP0Eujll4fW73"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fa1d900c","parentId":"a0090643","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5eaa5601-77bb-4677-99e8-ad29861a1f67","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 527 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if neede"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1366,"aggregated":"<img src=\"/src/assets/sprite-monkey-idle-4x-v2.png\" alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"h-7 w-7 rounded-full border border-violet/50 object-cover\"/>\n<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Life Support Officer\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Systems Engineer\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>\n<img alt=\"Station Archivist\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059374371}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c6a8d72","parentId":"fa1d900c","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Found the sprite bug!** The sidebar `<img>` has `src=\"/src/assets/sprite-monkey-idle-4x-v2.png\"` but the StationRoom agent sprites have **no `src` attribute at all** — they render as `<img alt=\"Space Monkey\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>`.\n\nThis means `agentSprite` (the `sprite` prop) is **empty string** on the server side. The issue is in how `SPRITES` is populated in `AgentOffice.tsx` — it's done in a `useEffect` which only runs on the client, so the SSR render gets empty strings.\n\nLet me verify this theory:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2e789956-5284-4b2d-b83f-3bf80819b407","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && sed -n '95,115p' src/components/AgentOffice.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && sed -n '95,115p' src/components/AgentOffice.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":527,"output":211,"cacheRead":79744,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80482,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059374373,"responseId":"gen-1780059374-pMruvHh7iuzme0o0YdDq"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4edc7c9","parentId":"5c6a8d72","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"2e789956-5284-4b2d-b83f-3bf80819b407","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 734 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if neede"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"}, []);\n  // Always live — no toggle\n  const [nowRunning, setNowRunning] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [upNext, setUpNext] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const [chatter, setChatter] = useState(\"\");\n  // Always live mode — no ambient timer needed\n\n  // Load sprites from crew\n  useEffect(() => {\n    CREW.forEach(c => {\n      SPRITES[c.id] = { idle: c.sprites.idle, working: c.sprites.working, walking: c.sprites.walking, away: c.sprites.idle };\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  // Live data is always used directly\n\n  // Dispatch live data updates (but don't override seeded initial data on first render)\n  const initialDataSeeded = useRef(false);\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!initialDataSeeded.current) {\n      initialDataSeeded.current = true;","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059399636}}
{"type":"message","id":"d42c370e","parentId":"d4edc7c9","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Confirmed!** The `SPRITES` object is populated inside `useEffect(() => {...}, [])` which doesn't run during SSR. The SSR render sees `SPRITES` as an empty object, so `SPRITES[room.occupantId]?.idle` returns `undefined`, and the `<img src={undefined}>` renders without a `src` attribute.\n\nThe fix: populate `SPRITES` outside of `useEffect`, at module level or during render.\n\nNow let me also understand issue #2 — the Scheduler page. The SSR returns the route fine (match ID `schedulerscheduler`), the HTML shows only a spinner, and the `scheduler.tsx` has a `loading` state defaulting to true via `useCronData()`. Let me check what `useCronData` returns:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"240ae7a8-72cf-4ad3-8411-573e5cbfa347","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"bd48f61c-2632-4ad8-b855-05ebf426b93e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":435,"output":255,"cacheRead":80256,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80946,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059399639,"responseId":"gen-1780059399-16vQYSMte149FuQ0QgIw"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0f0dd96","parentId":"d42c370e","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"240ae7a8-72cf-4ad3-8411-573e5cbfa347","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 8572 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059433266}}
{"type":"message","id":"76793405","parentId":"c0f0dd96","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"bd48f61c-2632-4ad8-b855-05ebf426b93e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 3398 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"import type { OpenClawCronJob } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { CronError } from \"./useCronData\";\nimport { Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport { Power, Clock, AlertTriangle, CheckCircle, Loader2 } from \"lucide-react\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface CronJobCardProps {\n  job: OpenClawCronJob;\n  isToggling: boolean;\n  hasResult: boolean;\n  resultMessage: string | null;\n  hasActiveError: boolean;\n  onToggle: (job: OpenClawCronJob) => void;\n}\n\n// ── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function CronJobCard({\n  job,\n  isToggling,\n  hasResult,\n  resultMessage,\n  hasActiveError,\n  onToggle,\n}: CronJobCardProps) {\n  return (\n    <div\n      className={`rounded-xl border bg-card/60 px-5 py-4 transition-all ${\n        job.enabled\n          ? \"border-border border-l-4 border-l-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n          : \"border-border/40 border-l-4 border-l-border/30 opacity-70\"\n      }`}\n    >\n      <div className=\"flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap\">\n          <h3 className=\"font-semibold\">{job.name}</h3>\n          <Pill variant={job.enabled ? \"online\" : \"default\"}>\n            {job.enabled ? \"ACTIVE\" : \"DISABLED\"}\n          </Pill>\n          {hasActiveError && (\n            <Pill variant=\"warning\">⚠ {job.consecutiveErrors ?? 0} error{job.consecutiveErrors ?? 0 > 1 ? \"s\" : \"\"}</Pill>\n          )}\n        </div>\n\n        <button\n          onClick={() => onToggle(job)}\n          disabled={isToggling}\n          className={`relative inline-flex h-6 w-11 items-center rounded-full transition-colors shrink-0 ${\n            job.enabled\n              ? \"bg-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n              : \"bg-muted-foreground/30\"\n          } ${isToggling ? \"opacity-50 cursor-wait\" : \"cursor-pointer\"}`}\n        >\n          {isToggling ? (\n            <Loader2 className=\"h-3 w-3 text-white absolute left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 animate-spin\" />\n          ) : (\n            <span\n              className={`inline-block h-4 w-4 transform rounded-full bg-white transition-transform ${\n                job.enabled ? \"translate-x-6\" : \"translate-x-1\"\n              }`}\n            />\n          )}\n        </button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div className=\"mt-2 flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground\">\n        <Clock className=\"h-3 w-3\" />\n        <span>{job.schedule}</span>\n      </div>\n\n      {job.message && (\n        <div className=\"mt-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 line-clamp-2\">\n          {job.message}\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      <div className=\"mt-3 flex items-center gap-4 font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground/50\">\n        {job.lastRun !== \"—\" && (\n          <span>Last: {new Date(job.lastRun).toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"2-digit\", month: \"short\", hour: \"2-digit\", minute: \"2-digit\" })}</span>\n        )}\n        {job.nextRun !== \"—\" && job.enabled && (\n          <span>Next: {new Date(job.nextRun).toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"2-digit\", month: \"short\", hour: \"2-digit\", minute: \"2-digit\" })}</span>\n        )}\n      </div>\n\n      {hasResult && resultMessage && (\n        <div className={`mt-2 text-xs ${resultMessage.startsWith(\"Failed\") ? \"text-destructive\" : \"text-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"}`}>\n          {resultMessage}\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780059433267}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e47b0a3","parentId":"76793405","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK so the Scheduler page loads data client-side via `useCronData` which fetches `/api/crons` and `/api/cron-errors`. The page renders fine on the server (shows a spinner), but the client-side fetch might be failing. Let me check the API endpoint:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"938f4684-d5a3-41c6-b788-1d1e18a6d0d9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/crons | head -5","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/crons | head -5\", \"timeout\": 10}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3d0ffd64-76f1-43a7-be63-3eb03452f39c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/api/crons && echo \"\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/api/cron-errors && echo \"\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://localhost:3000/api/crons && echo \\\"\\\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://localhost:3000/api/cron-errors && echo \\\"\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":3359,"output":203,"cacheRead":80640,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":84202,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780059433270,"responseId":"gen-1780059433-CokNOLIGBX99RgiCU5RE"}}
