{"type":"message","id":"6cde095e","parentId":"33939f16","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Only one route file. But the `scheduler/` directory exists alongside `scheduler.tsx`. In TanStack Router's file-based routing, when you have BOTH `src/routes/scheduler.tsx` and `src/routes/scheduler/`, the directory might be treated as a route group or layout that wraps the file-based route, causing the double ID.\n\nActually, looking at the error logs from earlier:\n```\nWarning: Route file \"src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\" does not export a Route.\nWarning: Route file \"src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\" does not export a Route.\n```\n\nTanStack Router is scanning the `scheduler/` directory and finding `CronJobCard.tsx` and `useCronData.ts` as potential route files (they match `.tsx`/`.ts` pattern). They don't export a Route, so they generate warnings. But the directory itself might be creating a phantom route node.\n\nThe real issue is likely that the `scheduler/` directory is interfering with the route tree. The fix is to either:\n1. Move `CronJobCard.tsx` and `useCronData.ts` out of the `scheduler/` directory (e.g., to `src/components/scheduler/` or `src/routes/scheduler-page/`)\n2. Or rename the directory so it doesn't conflict\n\nNow I have both root causes identified. Let me fix them."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"01c1ba1b-b699-409a-bef4-cda276316856","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"plan":[{"step":"Investigate sprite issue — compare Dashboard vs Teams sprite loading","status":"completed"},{"step":"Investigate Scheduler page routing issue","status":"completed"},{"step":"Fix sprite issue: move SPRITES init out of useEffect","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Fix scheduler: move non-route files out of scheduler/ dir","status":"pending"},{"step":"Verify all routes return 200","status":"pending"},{"step":"Commit and push","status":"pending"}],"explanation":"Root causes identified:\\n1. Sprites: SPRI