{"type":"message","id":"9fd2c68c","parentId":"d3c9a8c6","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both issues fixed and pushed. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis & Fixes\n\n### Issue 1: Agent Sprites Missing on Dashboard/AgentOffice\n\n**Cause:** The `SPRITES` map in `AgentOffice.tsx` was populated inside a `useEffect(() => {...}, [])` hook — which only runs on the client, not during SSR. When the server rendered the page, `SPRITES` was still an empty object, so `SPRITES[room.occupantId]?.idle` returned `undefined`. This produced `<img>` tags with **no `src` attribute** at all.\n\n**Fix:** Moved the `CREW.forEach(...)` initialization of `SPRITES` outside the `useEffect`, so it runs at module load time — available to both SSR and client.\n\n### Issue 2: Scheduler Page Not Loading\n\n**Cause:** Having both `src/routes/scheduler.tsx` (route file) AND `src/routes/scheduler/` (directory with `.tsx`/`.ts` files) confused TanStack Router's file-based routing. It scanned `CronJobCard.tsx` and `useCronData.ts` as potential route files (they don't export a `Route`), generating warnings AND creating a route ID collision (`schedulerscheduler`). The client-side hydration then failed, leaving only a spinner visible.\n\n**Fix:** Moved `CronJobCard.tsx` and `useCronData.ts` from `src/routes/scheduler/` to `src/components/scheduler/` (a non-route directory), and updated imports in `scheduler.tsx`.\n\n### Verification\n- ✅ All 5 routes return 200: `/`, `/visual`, `/scheduler`, `/tasks`, `/team`\n- ✅ All 4 agent sprites have valid `src` attributes in SSR'd HTML\n- ✅ Scheduler page renders with full content (15,960 bytes, no spinner)\n- ✅ Committed and pushed to `origin/main` (commit `18bfb94`)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":187,"output":423,"cacheRead":154496,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":155106,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780060474986,"responseId":"gen-1780060475-iIgJP1gnLBObKzzvGbVF"}}
