{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\n\nAdditional context from HEARTBEAT.md:\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- If a task is already `in_progress` and was started >2 hours ago with no progress update, reset it to backlog\n\n## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\nCurrent time: Friday, May 29th, 2026 - 2:42 PM (Europe/London)\nReference UTC: 2026-05-29 13:42 UTC","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"883e359a","parentId":"866ab036","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"d58a3635","parentId":"883e359a","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"6be8e69e-356c-4754-905d-135e96805080","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ntasks = json.load(sys.stdin)\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'backlog']\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\nprint(f'Backlog: {len(backlog)}, In-progress: {len(in_progress)}')\nfor t in backlog:\n    print(f'  BACKLOG: {t.get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"?\\\")} (id={t.get(\\\"id\\\",\\\"?\\\")})')\nfor t in in_progress:\n    print(f'  IN_PROGRESS: {t.get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"?\\\")} (id={t.get(\\\"id\\\",\\\"?\\\")})')\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No tasks.json or parse error\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\ntasks = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'backlog']\\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\\nprint(f'Backlog: {len(backlog)}, In-progress: {len(in_progress)}')\\nfor t in backlog:\\n    print(f'  BACKLOG: {t.get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")} (id={t.get(\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")})')\\nfor t in in_progress:\\n    print(f'  IN_PROGRESS: {t.get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")} (id={t.get(\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")})')\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No tasks.json or parse error\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":106844,"output":205,"cacheRead":7808,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":114857,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780062145000,"responseId":"gen-1780062145-ZySRztk7rgCXM4GYgmnq