{"type":"message","id":"0743915d","parentId":"1cf79356","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I can see the full HTML now. The room containers have:\n1. `<canvas width=\"768\" height=\"512\">` — room backgrounds (drawn client-side via JS)\n2. `<div class=\"agent-idle\"><img src=\"...sprite...\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" /></div>` — agent sprites\n\nLooking at the sprite markup: the `<img>` has no border or background. But the **parent room container** has `bg-card/10` which gives `background: oklch(... card color / 0.1)`. And the `agent-idle` class only has an animation, no background.\n\nThe grey box the user sees is likely from the room container itself (`bg-card/10`) applied to the room container `<div className=\"relative overflow-hidden bg-card/10\">`. The pixel art PNG sprites have transparent backgrounds, so whatever is behind them (the grey `bg-card/10` background) shows through the transparent areas or the entire room containers have a grey tint over the transparent image edges.\n\nBut wait — the `bg-card/10` background is applied to the **room container** div, not the sprite div. The `<img>` sits inside the room and should show through transparent areas with whatever bg is behind it in the room canvas.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the HTML structure: the sprite `<img>` is inside `<div class=\"agent-idle\">` which is inside `relative z-10` div inside `relative bg-card/10` div. The `bg-card/10` is the room container background. So the sprite PNG with transparent background will show `bg-card/10` through its transparent parts — but that's the very faint oklch card color, not a \"grey box.\"\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user says \"grey box around the sprites.\" This might be the `rounded-lg border` CSS class on the agent sprite img in Spacestation.tsx. Wait no — looking at StationRoom line 196: `<img src={agentSprite} alt={agentName} className=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style={{ imageRendering: \"pixelated\", ...}} />` — no border.\n\nBut the Spacestation.tsx AgentSprite component (line 295) has `rounded-lg border-2` and border color styles. Let me check if AgentOffice uses Spacestation or StationRoom:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"823d1af6-19f3-4b21-8b6b-17a9ce47e6fc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && grep \"Spacestation\\|StationRoom\" src/components/AgentOffice.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && grep \\\"Spacestation\\\\|StationRoom\\\" src/components/AgentOffice.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":16496,"output":579,"cacheRead":138368,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":155443,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780064433748,"responseId":"gen-1780064434-yNuklUkNBeXkpq5F8Kxn"}}
