{"type":"message","id":"09b66036","parentId":"beb05742","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — AgentOffice.tsx uses `StationRoom`, not `Spacestation`. The StationRoom component renders sprites with `<img src={agentSprite} className=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" />` — no border or background on the image itself.\n\nThe grey box might be a rendering artifact from the browser or a CSS `background-color` on one of the wrapper elements. The room container has `bg-card/10` which gives it a subtle background color. This might appear as a grey box if the canvas isn't drawn fast enough or if there's a mismatch.\n\nWait — I think I may be overcomplicating this. The user might have seen the grey boxes in the **browser**, not in the HTML/CSS. The room backgrounds (`bg-card/10`) could appear as grey boxes when the canvas room drawings haven't rendered yet (client-side only). And the sprite \"grey box\" could be the `bg-card/10` of the room container showing around/behind the sprite.\n\nLet me reassess the user's issues based on what I can verify in the SSR HTML:\n\n1. **Room backgrounds**: Canvas elements exist, will draw on client-side via `useEffect`. This should work unless hydration fails.\n2. **Grey box around sprites**: No explicit border/bg on sprite `<img>`. The room container `bg-card/10` might appear as a grey backdrop.\n3. **Scheduler spinner**: The SSR HTML for /scheduler shows it should render fine with the cron data.\n\nAll three issues might be **client-side hydration problems**. Let me check if there's a hydration error by looking at what the browser client-side would see. But I can't access a browser console directly. Let me check if there's a mismatch between SSR and client renders.\n\nActually — looking at line 219 of AgentOffice.tsx: `bgImage=\"\"`. An empty string is passed as `bgImage` to StationRoom. When `useCanvas={true}`, StationRoom ignores `bgImage` and renders `<RoomCanvas>` instead. So the room background depends entirely on the client-side canvas drawing. \n\nLet me focus on what I can actually verify and fix. Let me check if the Spacestation page (/visual) has the same issue:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"cdcd5ef2-6ddf-4ed2-91ea-fe66f310a748","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/visual && echo \"\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://localhost:3000/visual && echo \\\"\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2ddc7811-aa36-41ae-87c0-9f93c421595c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3000/scheduler | strings | grep -oP '\"i\":\"[^\"]*\"' | head -5","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s http://localhost:3000/scheduler | strings | grep -oP '\\\"i\\\":\\\"[^\\\"]*\\\"' | head -5\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":718,"output":576,"cacheRead":154752,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":156046,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780064493618,"responseId":"gen-1780064493-F5gdQZfs04JO5mIAXEDT"}}
