{"type":"message","id":"07f439ed","parentId":"eaa8bfd2","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Files are in place. The dev server should have hot-reloaded. Let me check the actual content of the scheduler page more carefully — maybe the issue is that the `loading` state in `useCronData` starts as `true`, shows a spinner, and the API fetch completes but the re-render doesn't happen. But that's a client-side issue I can't debug without a browser.\n\nLet me take a step back. The user is reporting these issues from their browser. I can verify SSR works, but I can't see client-side JS errors. Let me focus on things I **can** fix and verify:\n\n1. **Room backgrounds**: The canvas rendering is client-side only. If the browser JS isn't running (hydration error), rooms won't draw. The canvas elements ARE present in SSR HTML though. I can't fix hydration without seeing the error.\n\n2. **Grey box around sprites**: Let me look more carefully. The sprite `<img>` has `w-20 h-20 object-contain`. If the room container has `bg-card/10`, and the sprite image has transparent areas, the room background might bleed through. But the user says \"grey box around sprites\" which sounds like a CSS border/background on a wrapper element. Let me check the Spacestation component (used on the /visual page):"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"d56e3730-0288-42e2-9a3a-90e2ad6b6231","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"offset":290,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/Spacestation.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 20, \"offset\": 290, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/Spacestation.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":483,"output":334,"cacheRead":156672,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":157489,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"