{"type":"message","id":"7e217647","parentId":"dd36767f","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Found it!** `Spacestation.tsx` line 296: `className={`w-14 h-14 rounded-lg border-2 object-cover pixel-room ${...}`}` — this has `border-2` and `rounded-lg` on the sprite `<img>`. And the `pixel-room` class applies `image-rendering: pixelated`.\n\nBut AgentOffice uses `StationRoom`, not `Spacestation`. Let me re-check the StationRoom sprite rendering — the HTML output shows `<img src=\"...\" class=\"w-20 h-20 object-contain\" style=\"image-rendering:pixelated\"/>` — no border or rounded corners.\n\nWait, let me re-examine. The user said this is something they see in the browser. All three issues (room backgrounds, grey box, scheduler spinner) might share a common root cause: **client-side hydration failure**. If the JavaScript doesn't execute properly on the client:\n- Canvas room drawings won't render (blank/empty rooms)\n- Sprites might show error states or placeholder boxes\n- Scheduler data won't load (infinite spinner)\n\nLet me check if there's a hydration mismatch. A common cause is when SSR renders something different from what the client expects. Let me look for potential issues:\n\nThe SPRITES object is now initialized at the top of the component function body (not inside useEffect). This means it runs during SSR — which is what we want. But let me verify the component works correctly end-to-end.\n\nLet me try a different approach — let me check if Vite dev server is actually serving my latest code:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"c0d8f88e-9c40-4257-8ae6-1381e1c65e91","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/components/AgentOffice.tsx | head -110 | tail -15","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/components/AgentOffice.tsx | head -110 | tail -15\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"opena