{"type":"message","id":"cddb393d","parentId":"39a4e4c5","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"6cdb0c81-6c8b-497e-b14e-9e5e6504f1a9","toolName":"update_plan","content":[],"details":{"status":"updated","explanation":"Room backgrounds are canvas-drawn client-side, SSR HTML has empty canvas elements - this is by design. Need to check if CSS/bg colors are creating visible grey boxes around sprites during hydration. Scheduler works in SSR. All three issues are likely client-side hydration problems.","plan":[{"step":"Investigate room backgrounds (canvas rendering)","status":"completed"},{"step":"Fix grey box around sprites","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Fix scheduler still showing spinner","status":"pending"},{"step":"Commit all fixes","status":"pending"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780065203070}}
{"type":"message","id":"a91e227b","parentId":"cddb393d","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me look at what could cause the grey box. The sprites have transparent PNG backgrounds. The room container div has `bg-card/10`. But `bg-card/10` would tint the entire room area very lightly. Let me check the CSS:\n\nThe `StationRoom` wraps everything in `<div className=\"relative overflow-hidden bg-card/10\">` — this applies a semi-transparent card background color to the entire room. On top of this, the `<canvas>` draws the room art. But the canvas draws with its own opaque colors (floor, walls, etc). The `bg-card/10` should only show through where the canvas is transparent.\n\nBut wait — during SSR, the canvas is empty. The client-side JS draws on it in `useEffect`. Between page load and JS execution, the user sees the empty canvas with `bg-card/10` behind it — this would look like a grey box. And the sprite `<img>` on top would show the grey background through its transparent parts.\n\nActually, the sprites have `object-contain` and `w-20 h-20`. If the image has exact pixel art with no padding, `object-contain` should show the sprite with transparent areas. The grey the user sees is likely the `bg-card/10` background color bleeding through.\n\nBut wait — this would have been an issue before my changes too. Unless the room canvases previously drew their backgrounds faster, or the `bg-card/10` wasn't there before. Let me check git history for when `bg-card/10` was added to StationRoom:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"bd3ab049-490d-4cef-b172-24787e37ef3f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline --all -- src/components/StationRoom.tsx | head -10","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log --oneline --all -- src/components/StationRoom.tsx | head -10\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b02e0c16-68b7-4a5d-ad59-907a72dbdc44","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log -1 --format=\"%h %s\" -- src/components/StationRoom.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git log -1 --format=\\\"%h %s\\\" -- src/components/StationRoom.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":279,"output":445,"cacheRead":160768,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":161492,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780065203076,"responseId":"gen-1780065203-7U08skfy8EqJ6ks7LTHS"}}
