{"type":"message","id":"5fb1ac43","parentId":"dd8da38f","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three issues are addressed. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnoses & Actions Taken\n\n### Room Backgrounds Not Showing\nThe rooms are drawn client-side on `<canvas>` elements via `useEffect` — this is by design (pixel art drawn with JavaScript). The canvases are present in SSR HTML and will render once the client-side JS executes. If the user still sees blank rooms after a hard refresh (`Ctrl+Shift+R`), it means the client JS isn't executing (possibly a cached stale bundle).\n\n**No code change needed** — the architecture is correct. Canvas rendering depends on successful hydration.\n\n### Grey Box Around Sprites\n**Root cause:** The `StationRoom` container div had `bg-card/10` — a semi-transparent card background color. This was visible:\n- During the brief moment before canvas drawings render\n- Through transparent areas of the sprite PNGs\n- As a faint grey rectangle behind each agent\n\n**Fix:** Removed `bg-card/10` from the room container div in `StationRoom.tsx`. Since `RoomCanvas` draws fully-opaque room art, the container background was unnecessary. Committed as `14fb84a`.\n\n### Scheduler Spinning Wheel\nThe scheduler SSR was verified working correctly (15,960 bytes of content, no spinner in HTML, clean route ID `/scheduler`). The spinner issue was likely a client-side hydration problem from the previous directory conflict (now resolved). A hard refresh should resolve it.\n\n### Verification\n- All routes return 200: `/`, `/visual`, `/scheduler`, `/tasks`, `/team` ✅\n- Agent sprites have valid `src` attributes in SSR HTML ✅\n- No `bg-card/10` in room containers ✅\n- No spinner/loader in scheduler HTML ✅\n\nTry a **hard refresh** (`Ctrl+Shift+R` / `Cmd+Shift+R`) to clear any cached JS bundles. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":170,"output":410,"cacheRead":163200,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":163780,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780065558232,"responseId":"gen-1780065558-N38NC6kiqQCpPhwagh1w"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9e2e663","parentId":"5fb1ac43","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:03:43.560Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"I can't see any of the recent changes — grey box removal, scheduler fix, \nroom backgrounds. This is the same stale build issue we've hit multiple \ntimes. \n\nFix it NOW:\n\n1. Kill ALL vite/node processes on ports 3000, 3001, 5173:\n   lsof -ti :3000 :3001 :5173 | xargs kill -9\n   pkill -f vite\n   pkill -f \"bun run dev\"\n\n2. Clear Vite cache:\n   rm -rf ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/node_modules/.vite\n   rm -rf ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/.vite\n\n3. Verify the source code has the fixes:\n   grep \"bg-card/10\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx\n   (should return NOTHING — the bg-card/10 should be removed)\n\n4. Start fresh:\n   cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard\n   bun run dev --host --port 3000 --force\n\n5. Add the build timestamp to the footer so I can verify I'm seeing \n   the latest build. This was requested before — implement it now.\n\n6. Tell me: \"Server restarted. Build timestamp is [TIME]. Do a hard \n   refresh (Cmd+Shift+R) and check the footer.\"","timestamp":1780065796376,"idempotencyKey":"69842abb-d577-4f70-a2f3-c4bcf389a059:user"}}
