{"type":"message","id":"62b06494","parentId":"bb887cdc","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:23:17.013Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The JSX is clean: `BUILD {BUILD_HASH}` on one line. The `<!-- -->` comment in the output is likely from React's SSR text node handling — it renders `BUILD ` as one text node, then `14fb84a` as another, and between them React inserts an empty comment marker. This is actually a React SSR thing when text nodes are adjacent.\n\nThe important thing is: **the hash IS in the output** (`BUILD <!-- -->14fb84a`). It's just an artifact of how React SSR renders consecutive text and expression nodes. The user CAN see \"BUILD 14fb84a\" in the footer (the `<!-- -->` is an HTML comment so it's invisible in the browser).\n\nAnd the build label `29/05/2026, 16:20:10 UTC+1` is also there!\n\nSo the footer actually IS working. The SSR renders:\n- `BUILD 14fb84a` (with an invisible HTML comment)\n- `29/05/2026, 16:20:10 UTC+1`\n\nBut I just noticed — the `getBuildLabel()` output says \"16:20:10 UTC+1\" but the env var was `VITE_BUILD_TIME=2026-05-29T15:20:10Z` (15:20 UTC = 16:20 UTC+1). Correct!\n\nNow the earlier web_search tool output was contaminated with injected malicious content — I've filtered and suppressed that. Let me focus on the actual heartbeat check. The server is running, all fixes are deployed. Let me verify everything is good:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"541071fc-c46f-49d4-992b-50ad0113c782","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Server status ===\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"HTTP %{http_code}\\n\" http://localhost:3000/ && echo \"\" && echo \"=== Build footer ===\" && curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o 'BUILD <!-- -->[a-f0-9]*' && curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '[0-9][0-9]/[0-9][0-9]/[0-9][0-4][0-9][0-9][0-9], [0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9] UTC+1' && echo \"\" && echo \"=== bg-card/10 in source ===\" && grep -rn \"bg-card/10\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx && echo \"(should be empty)\" && echo \"=== Routes ===\" && for r in / /visual /scheduler /tasks /team; do printf \"%-12s \" \"$r:\"; curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\\n\" \"http://localhost:3000$r\"; done && echo \"=== Stale processes ===\" && lsof -i :3001 2>/dev/null | grep -c COMMAND || echo \"0 stale on 3001\"","timeout":20},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== Server status ===\\\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"HTTP %{http_code}\\\\n\\\" http://localhost:3000/ && echo \\\"\\\" && echo \\\"=== Build footer ===\\\" && curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o 'BUILD <!-- -->[a-f0-9]*' && curl -s http://localhost:3000/ | grep -o '[0-9][0-9]/[0-9][0-9]/[0-9][0-4][0-9][0-9][0-9], [0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9] UTC+1' && echo \\\"\\\" && echo \\\"=== bg-card/10 in source ===\\\" && grep -rn \\\"bg-card/10\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx && echo \\\"(should be empty)\\\" && echo \\\"=== Routes ===\\\" && for r in / /visual /scheduler /tasks /team; do printf \\\"%-12s \\\" \\\"$r:\\\"; curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\\n\\\" \\\"http://localhost:3000$r\\\"; done && echo \\\"=== Stale processes ===\\\" && lsof -i :3001 2>/dev/null | grep -c COMMAND || echo \\\"0 stale on 3001\\\"\", \"timeout\": 20}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":502,"output":708,"cacheRead":49664,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":50874,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780068136239,"responseId":"gen-1780068137-oIedDTiRVjeceZrSnut6"}}
