{"type":"message","id":"80695747","parentId":"f5349c2c","timestamp":"2026-05-29T19:31:44.053Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Line 3** imports `getActivityFeed` and `getAwaitingReviewCount` from `@/lib/server-data`. This is `server-data.ts` which does `export * from \"./server-data/helpers\"`, and `helpers.ts` imports `node:fs`. Vite's bundler sees this import chain and tries to bundle `node:fs` into the client — boom.\n\nBut these are **server functions** (they use `fs` to read files). The Dashboard is importing them as if they're client-callable. The fix: Dashboard should NOT import server-side data functions directly. It should fetch data via API routes or loaders.\n\nLet me check what `getActivityFeed` and `getAwaitingReviewCount` actually do:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"58e7b8d4-9ca7-4294-bd33-ca521a64afbe","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"export.*getActivityFeed\\|export.*getAwaitingReviewCount\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -n \\\"export.*getActivityFeed\\\\|export.*getAwaitingReviewCount\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"5a592500-0ac6-45c2-9a19-4c01023eb65c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"getActivityFeed\\|getAwaitingReviewCount\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/activity.ts | head -5","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -n \\\"getActivityFeed\\\\|getAwaitingReviewCount\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/activity.ts | head -5\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":47866,"output":264,"cacheRead":9216,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":57346,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestam