{"type":"message","id":"549f1651","parentId":"6acb40c3","timestamp":"2026-05-29T19:43:27.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Dashboard component at line 268 still calls `getAwaitingReviewCount()` — but that import is now commented out. This will cause a runtime error. The whole Dashboard data flow needs to be fixed properly. Let me see the full picture:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2b8c1192-5f58-40e8-9d86-d1988473abcf","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/index.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/index.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":874,"output":87,"cacheRead":62208,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":63169,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780083798926,"responseId":"gen-1780083799-hG7MH3kuBJFn7rysulDc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a42e9f11","parentId":"549f1651","timestamp":"2026-05-29T19:43:27.065Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"2b8c1192-5f58-40e8-9d86-d1988473abcf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { createFileRoute } from \"@tanstack/react-router\";\nimport { Dashboard } from \"@/components/Dashboard\";\nimport { getSystemStats, getAgentStatus, getActivityFeed } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { ActivityEvent } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\n\nexport const Route = createFileRoute(\"/\")({\n  head: () => ({ meta: [{ title: \"Mission Control — Dashboard\" }] }),\n  loader: async () => {\n    const [stats, agents] = await Promise.all([\n      getSystemStats(),\n      getAgentStatus(),\n    ]);\n    let activity: ActivityEvent[] = [];\n    try { activity = await getActivityFeed(); } catch { /* ignore */ }\n\n    return { agents, stats, activity };\n  },\n  component: HomePage,\n});\n\nfunction HomePage() {\n  const { agents, stats, activity } = Route.useLoaderData();\n  return (\n    <Dashboard\n      agents={agents}\n      systemStats={stats}\n      activity={activity}\n    />\n  );\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780083807065}}
{"type":"message","id":"87dda07e","parentId":"a42e9f11","timestamp":"2026-05-29T19:43:43.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the full picture. The `index.tsx` **route** also imports `getSystemStats`, `getAgentStatus`, `getActivityFeed` from `@/lib/server-data`. These are `createServerFn` server functions that use `node:fs`. In TanStack Start, server functions in route loaders should be fine — they run on the server. The problem is when these leak into the **client bundle**.\n\nThe real issue: the `server-data.ts` barrel file exports both pure helper functions (`readFileOrNull`, `readJsonOrNull`, etc.) AND server functions (`getActivityFeed`, etc.) from the same module. When any client component imports types or functions from this barrel, Vite tries to resolve the entire module including the `node:fs` imports.\n\nThe fix needs to be architectural: **separate the server-only code from shared types/utilities**. Let me check what's imported where:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"bcef4587-d0de-499c-bbb3-23784c1de5c8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && echo \"=== Who imports from server-data? ===\" && grep -rn \"from.*@/lib/server-data\\\"$\\|from.*@/lib/server-data\\\"\" src/ --include=\"*.tsx\" --include=\"*.ts\" | grep -v node_modules && echo \"\" && echo \"=== Who imports types from server-data? ===\" && grep -rn \"import.*type.*from.*server-data\" src/ --include=\"*.tsx\" --include=\"*.ts\" | grep -v node_modules","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && echo \\\"=== Who imports from server-data? ===\\\" && grep -rn \\\"from.*@/lib/server-data\\\\\\\"$\\\\|from.*@/lib/server-data\\\\\\\"\\\" src/ --include=\\\"*.tsx\\\" --include=\\\"*.ts\\\" | grep -v node_modules && echo \\\"\\\" && echo \\\"=== Who imports types from server-data? ===\\\" && grep -rn \\\"import.*type.*from.*server-data\\\" src/ --include=\\\"*.ts