{"type":"message","id":"cae41111","parentId":"97484320","timestamp":"2026-05-29T19:43:58.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a big problem. Many components import directly from `@/lib/server-data`, and the barrel export re-exports everything from `helpers.ts` which imports `node:fs`. Even type-only imports from the barrel can cause Vite to resolve the full module.\n\nThe root cause is the barrel `server-data/index.ts` line 4: `export * from \"./helpers\"`. This drags `node:fs` into every import chain.\n\n**The fix:** Create a clean types-only export path so components never need to import the server-data barrel for types. The pure functions from helpers (`readFileOrNull`, etc.) should NOT be in the public barrel.\n\nLet me fix this properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"845d5597-2d69-4d59-a140-a73b73af3cbf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/lib/server-data/index.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && cat src/lib/server-data/index.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1464,"output":181,"cacheRead":63360,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":65005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780083823273,"responseId":"gen-1780083823-fzNAgLDTcOkj2aYYzS6w"}}
