{"type":"message","id":"9592f216","parentId":"39c834f2","timestamp":"2026-05-29T19:59:13.731Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The scheduler is loading. Now audit the 4 cron jobs:\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n1. DAILY STATION CHECK — DISABLED, 1 ERROR\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThis says \"Do NOT use any AI model calls\" but previously it was \ntiming out on model calls. Fix it:\n- Make it TRULY shell-only — verify no model calls are possible\n- Fix the error (check logs for what failed on May 21)\n- Enable it — this is our daily sitrep to Telegram\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n2. SESSIONS CLEANUP — DISABLED\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThis was supposed to replace the old `openclaw sessions cleanup` \ncron. Is it needed? We already have maintenance.sh handling cleanup.\n- If maintenance.sh covers this: DELETE this cron job\n- If not: enable it\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n3. SESSION AUTO-EXPIRY — DISABLED\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nSame question — is maintenance.sh already doing this?\n- If yes: DELETE\n- If no: enable it\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n4. AUTO-UPDATE FREERIDE + AIDER — ACTIVE, WORKING\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThis is running daily at 06:00 and last ran successfully May 29. \nKeep it. But:\n- Move it to a shell-only LaunchAgent instead of a cron job \n  (same pattern as maintenance.sh — no isolated sessions)\n- Or confirm it's already shell-only with no model calls\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nAFTER AUDIT\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThe scheduler should show ONLY:\n- Daily Station Check (enabled, shell-only, working)\n- Auto-update FreeRide + Aider (enabled, shell-only)\n- Everything else deleted or consolidated into maintenance.sh\n\nReport what you kept, deleted, and enabled.","timestamp":1780084752977,"idempotencyKey":"686e2fd1-8f17-4103-9e16-b026ba7b8f22:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e4ed088","parentId":"9592f216","timestamp":"2026-05-29T20:00:10.553Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me audit all 4 cron jobs. First, let me read their actual task definitions and check what maintenance.sh already covers."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"9bc74e31-e56c-462e-9159-47207bd988d3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor t in data:\n    title = t.get('title','')\n    if any(k in title.lower() for k in ['station check', 'session cleanup', 'auto-expiry', 'freeride', 'aider']):\n        print(f\\\"--- {title} ---\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  status: {t.get('status')}\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  enabled: {t.get('enabled')}\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  schedule: {json.dumps(t.get('schedule',{}))}\\\")\n        desc = t.get('description','')\n        if desc:\n            print(f\\\"  description: {desc[:200]}\\\")\n        # Check for cron payload\n        payload = t.get('payload', {})\n        if payload:\n            print(f\\\"  payload.kind: {payload.get('kind')}\\\")\n            if payload.get('message'):\n                msg = payload['message']\n                print(f\\\"  payload.message: {msg[:300]}\\\")\n        print()\n\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nfor t in data:\\n    title = t.get('title','')\\n    if any(k in title.lower() for k in ['station check', 'session cleanup', 'auto-expiry', 'freeride', 'aider']):\\n        print(f\\\\\\\"--- {title} ---\\\\\\\")\\n        print(f\\\\\\\"  status: {t.get('status')}\\\\\\\")\\n        print(f\\\\\\\"  enabled: {t.get('enabled')}\\\\\\\")\\n        print(f\\\\\\\"  schedule: {json.dumps(t.get('schedule',{}))}\\\\\\\")\\n        desc = t.get('description','')\\n        if desc:\\n            print(f\\\\\\\"  description: {desc[:200]}\\\\\\\")\\n        # Check for cron payload\\n        payload = t.get('payload', {})\\n        if payload:\\n            print(f\\\\\\\"  payload.kind: {payload.get('kind')}\\\\\\\")\\n            if payload.get('message'):\\n                msg = payload['message']\\n                print(f\\\\\\\"  payload.message: {msg[:300]}\\\\\\\")\\n        print()\\n\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":68931,"output":283,"cacheRead":7808,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":77022,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780084753736,"responseId":"gen-1780084754-RvuAzZV5rfBZPmJ1uTRy"}}
