{"type":"message","id":"8a79ccd3","parentId":"a41fe080","timestamp":"2026-05-29T20:49:17.596Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `openclaw gateway status` output doesn't have \"sessions N\" on its own line. The session count comes from `openclaw status`, not `openclaw gateway status`. Let me fix the session count to use a different approach:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"34700935-f5c1-4514-ab41-8317b70accd1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/openclaw-status.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"    // Get real gateway status and session count\n    let gateway: string = \"unknown\";\n    let sessions: number = 0;\n    try {\n      const { execSync } = await import(\"node:child_process\");\n      const gwOut = execSync(\"openclaw gateway status 2>/dev/null\", { encoding: \"utf-8\" }).trim();\n      gateway = gwOut.toLowerCase().includes(\"running\") ? \"running\" : gwOut.toLowerCase().includes(\"stopped\") ? \"stopped\" : \"unknown\";\n      const sessMatch = gwOut.match(/sessions\\s+(\\d+)/i);\n      if (sessMatch) sessions = parseInt(sessMatch[1]) || 0;\n    } catch { /* fallback */ }","newText":"    // Get real gateway status\n    let gateway: string = \"unknown\";\n    try {\n      const { execSync } = await import(\"node:child_process\");\n      const gwOut = execSync(\"openclaw gateway status 2>/dev/null\", { encoding: \"utf-8\" }).trim();\n      gateway = gwOut.toLowerCase().includes(\"running\") ? \"running\" : gwOut.toLowerCase().includes(\"stopped\") ? \"stopped\" : \"unknown\";\n    } catch { /* fallback */ }\n\n    // Get session count from full status output\n    let sessions: number = 0;\n    try {\n      const { execSync } = await import(\"node:child_process\");\n      const statusOut = execSync(\"openclaw status 2>/dev/null\", { encoding: \"utf-8\" }).trim();\n      const sessMatch = statusOut.match(/sessions\\s+(\\d+)/i);\n      if (sessMatch) sessi