{"type":"message","id":"8d2ac3e4","parentId":"c2ab1497","timestamp":"2026-05-29T22:43:13.098Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The script uses `set -euo pipefail` — if `/Volumes/Public` isn't mounted, `mkdir -p` will fail and the script will exit with error. But the error goes to the server function's catch block which just returns `{ ok: false, size: \"failed\" }`. The button shows no meaningful error.\n\nLet me also check the `runBackup` handler to see how the result is returned to the client:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4d4909d2-d637-4f1f-9098-7aa39cd78887","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 10 \"export const runBackup\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/quick-actions.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -A 10 \\\"export const runBackup\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/quick-actions.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":451,"output":144,"cacheRead":103680,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":104275,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780094582920,"responseId":"gen-1780094583-srhLJzXIVUf6K5qXmOKT"}}
