{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\n\nAdditional context from HEARTBEAT.md:\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- If a task is already `in_progress` and was started >2 hours ago with no progress update, reset it to backlog\n\n## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\nCurrent time: Saturday, May 30th, 2026 - 1:12 PM (Europe/London)\nReference UTC: 2026-05-30 12:12 UTC","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"abeb336d","parentId":"cf7c0637","timestamp":"2026-05-30T12:12:24.925Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"175a7122","parentId":"abeb336d","timestamp":"2026-05-30T12:12:42.598Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHEARTBEAT.md has tasks. Let me check for backlog tasks and stale in-progress ones."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ce3051fe-a1f2-413d-8811-a003036e552f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\n\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nnow = datetime(2026, 5, 30, 12, 12, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\ngb_tz = timezone(timedelta(hours=1))  # Europe/London (BST = UTC+1 in May)\n\nbacklog = [t for t in data if t.get('status') == 'backlog']\nin_progress = [t for t in data if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\n\nprint(f'Backlog: {len(backlog)}')\nfor t in backlog:\n    print(f'  - {t.get(\\\"id\\\",\\\"?\\\")} — {t.get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"?\\\")[:80]}')\n\nprint(f'In Progress: {len(in_progress)}')\nfor t in in_progress:\n    started = t.get('startedAt', '')\n    stale = ''\n    if started:\n        try:\n            st = datetime.fromisoformat(started.replace('Z','+00:00'))\n            age_h = (now - st).total_seconds() / 3600\n            if age_h > 2:\n                stale = f' [STALE {age_h:.1f}h]'\n        except: pass\n    print(f'  - {t.get(\\\"id\\\",\\\"?\\\")} — {t.get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"?\\\")[:80]} (started: {started}){stale}')\n\"","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\\n\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nnow = datetime(2026, 5, 30, 12, 12, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\\ngb_tz = timezone(timedelta(hours=1))  # Europe/London (BST = UTC+1 in May)\\n\\nbacklog = [t for t in data if t.get('status') == 'backlog']\\nin_progress = [t for t in data if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\\n\\nprint(f'Backlog: {len(backlog)}')\\nfor t in backlog:\\n    print(f'  - {t.get(\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")} — {t.get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")[:80]}')\\n\\nprint(f'In Progress: {len(in_progress)}')\\nfor t in in_progress:\\n    started = t.get('startedAt', '')\\n    stale = ''\\n    if started:\\n        try:\\n            st = datetime.fromisoformat(started.replace('Z','+00:00'))\\n            age_h = (now - st).total_seconds() / 3600\\n            if age_h > 2:\\n                stale = f' [STALE {age_h:.1f}h]'\\n        except: pass\\n    print(f'  - {t.get(\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")} — {t.get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")[:80]} (started: {started}){stale}')\\n\\\"\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":95830,"output":373,"cacheRead":7680,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":103883,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780143144930,"responseId":"gen-1780143145-ezABHTX0cJm9mJa2BpLy"}}
